Notably missing:

* Probably a lot more

content.raw: If the enum is more specific it allows code to react to an error without parsing ReadableResult().
content.html: If the enum is more specific it allows code to react to an error without parsing ReadableResult().

content.raw:
otherwise, here are the enums I can think of:

~~~
        DELETE, // success
        DELETE_NOT_FOUND, // model does not exist
        DELETE_ERROR, // other errors, e.g. permission denied

        FETCH, // success
        FETCH_ALREADY_EXISTS, // model already exists
        FETCH_NOT_FOUND, // model not found
        FETCH_ERROR, // other errors

        UPLOAD, // success
        UPLOAD_ALREADY_EXISTS, // model already exists
        UPLOAD_ERROR // other errors
~~~

content.raw:
One `Result` class sounds like a better idea.

The enums could be pretty specific `NOT_DELETED_DNE, // deletion didn't happen because the model does not exist` or `FETCH_ALREADY_EXIST, // Model did not need to be fetched because it was already in cache`
content.html:

The enums could be pretty specific NOT_DELETED_DNE, // deletion didn't happen because the model does not exist or FETCH_ALREADY_EXIST, // Model did not need to be fetched because it was already in cache

content.raw: The `*Result` classes are very similar. Do you think the the implementation may diverge in the future? Otherwise we could just have a `Result` object with enum to identify the type of result.

content.raw: I'm a fan of identifying a model by a hash. A downside is if a really bad weakness in the hash algorithm is found in the future, every model might need to be given a new hash from a different algorithm.
content.html: I'm a fan of identifying a model by a hash. A downside is if a really bad weakness in the hash algorithm is found in the future, every model might need to be given a new hash from a different algorithm.

content.raw:
What's unique about a model is still something to work out. A scoped name of `org/usr/model_name` might conflict with the scoped name of nested models, or the world name. @iche033 and looked at grabcad.com appends to the model name string to make unique URLs: https://grabcad.com/library/bolt-and-nut-29

Idea is a user wants to name their model "car", but it's unique name might be "car-49" after it's uploaded.
